════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECURITY REMINDERS
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

✅ Add .env to .gitignore
✅ Add api_keys.json to .gitignore
✅ Use HTTPS in production
✅ Rotate keys every 90 days
✅ Deactivate compromised keys immediately
✅ Use different keys for dev/prod
✅ Never log actual keys (log hashes only)

❌ Don't commit .env
❌ Don't share keys in Slack/email
❌ Don't hardcode keys in code
❌ Don't use HTTP in production


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
EMERGENCY
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Key Compromised?
────────────────
1. python api_key_manager.py deactivate "KeyName"
2. Generate new key
3. Update .env
4. Restart Flask app
5. Notify affected users


Lost Access?
────────────
1. Generate new key: python api_key_manager.py create "Recovery"
2. Add to .env
3. Restart app


